subSubSection.paragraph:
Variation
. In the smallest female, the indentations on anterolateral margin form two strong teeth (
Fig. 74G
), while in the large females and males, the anterolateral margin is entire lined with sharper granules (
Figs. 72B
, 
75B
). The carapace proportions also appear to vary, with one specimen having a proportionately broader carapace (
Fig. 74D
).
